org.junit.jupiter.params.converter

Annotation Type JavaTimeConversionPattern


  • @Target(value={ANNOTATION_TYPE,PARAMETER})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Documented
 @API(status=EXPERIMENTAL,
     since="5.0")
 @ConvertWith(value=org.junit.jupiter.params.converter.JavaTimeArgumentConverter.class)
public @interface JavaTimeConversionPattern
    @JavaTimeConversionPattern is an annotation that allows a date/time conversion pattern to be specified on a method parameter of a @ParameterizedTest method.
    Since:
    5.0
    See Also:
    ParameterizedTest, DateTimeFormatterBuilder.appendPattern(String)
